# {{.Name}}

A {{.Example}} Go compute-module starter generated by `foundry-cmgo`.

## Local transform loop

```bash
go test ./...
go run ./cmd/compute-module local --input data/input.csv --output out/output.csv
```

The same `processor.Processor` implementation is used by local and Foundry modes.

## Mock Foundry data seeding

Copy a CSV into the mock Foundry dataset input layout:

```bash
foundry-cmgo seed dataset --csv data/input.csv --alias-map test/fixtures/alias-map.json --alias input
```
{{if .IsStream}}
Publish rows directly to the output stream when a mock Foundry server is running with that output RID registered as a stream:

```bash
foundry-cmgo seed stream --csv out/output.csv --alias-map test/fixtures/alias-map.json --alias output --url http://localhost:8080
```
{{end}}
## Foundry mode

This starter expects Foundry-style environment variables:

- `FOUNDRY_URL` for local mock shorthand, or `FOUNDRY_SERVICE_DISCOVERY_V2` for platform service discovery
- `BUILD2_TOKEN`
- `RESOURCE_ALIAS_MAP`

Run against the local mock server after seeding input data:

```bash
docker compose -f docker-compose.local.yml up --build --abort-on-container-exit
```

Or run the compute module directly if a mock Foundry server is already listening:

```bash
FOUNDRY_URL=http://localhost:8080 \
BUILD2_TOKEN=test/fixtures/token.txt \
RESOURCE_ALIAS_MAP=test/fixtures/alias-map.json \
go run ./cmd/compute-module foundry --output-mode {{.OutputMode}}
```

The output contract is intentionally small: `email,value,status` for dataset mode and equivalent JSON fields for stream mode.
